what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
This command sets up a secure shell (SSH) connection to an Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) instance using the specified user credentials and port forwarding. The "-i" option specifies the location of the private key file, "~/UserKey.pem". The "-C" option enables compression for faster transmission over slow networks. The "-L" option sets up a local tunnel to the remote server on port 25900, allowing applications running on the local machine to access resources on the EC2 instance as if they were directly connected.
